The paper deals with object detection, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). It also involves adversarial learning, which is a popular technique in deep learning (cs.LG). The proposed method involves exploiting deep semantic information and instance representations, which are key topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper applies the method to robotics (cs.RO) by evaluating it on a dataset of autonomous driving scenes.
